        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "Work in this class involves receiving, storing and issuing linens at an institution. Work assignments may be received from a working supervisor or employee may be expected to function independently under guidance or departmental policies, Employee assists superiors and plans work in order to expedite production, repair, and maintenance of supplies of fresh linen and other finished articles. May perform simple sewing operations. Tasks performed are largely repetitive in nature and are checked by a supervisor or departmental superior through spot inspections, review of operating reports, and analysis of comments expressed by those served and for adherence to departmental operating policies and efficient performance of duties",
